Press Releases.Title: 506 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 30 May 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 506 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore, the vast majority of whom are Work Permit holders residing in foreign worker dormitories. Based on our investigations so far, there are five cases in the community, of whom two are Singaporeans/Permanent Residents and three are Work Pass holders.  

2.     We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
30 MAY 2020
